## TL;DR: What Every 2.5ct Cushion Buyer Must Know First

The 2.5 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the cushion cluster's first genuinely statement size — at 8.5mm × 8.5mm face-up, it is unmistakable across a room, impossible to overlook at social distances, and commands a price in natural diamonds that shocks buyers who expected linear scaling from 2ct. Natural 2.5ct GIA G-VS1 Ideal quality starts at $19,375 from Blue Nile — a 40%+ jump over the comparable 2ct entry at $13,679. This is the size tier where every buying decision carries real financial consequence.

**Contrarian Truth — The Crushed Ice Trap:** Most 2.5ct cushion buyers default to the modified brilliant (crushed ice) sub-type because it dominates social media and Blue Nile's inventory. At 8.5mm face-up, the modified brilliant's uniform fine-sparkle pattern reads differently than it does at 6.5mm or 7.5mm — in some lighting conditions, particularly natural daylight, it can appear "glassy" or "wet" rather than energetic. The cushion brilliant (chunky facets) at 2.5ct often looks more visually arresting in person, and many buyers who see both sub-types side-by-side at this size choose the cushion brilliant — even if they originally wanted crushed ice.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Natural 2.5ct GIA G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$19,375](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29596947?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 2.5ct GIA F-VVS2 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$26,899](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29633630?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified (adjacent tier): **[$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 3ct GIA D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified (adjacent tier): **[$5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The entry point for natural buyers** is the [GIA 2.52ct G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $19,375](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29596947?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the lowest verified price for GIA Ideal quality at 2.5ct on Blue Nile. For lab buyers, 2.5ct modified brilliants sit in the $3,500–$5,000 range and deliver D-VVS1 Ideal quality for roughly one-fifth the natural price.

