## 2.5ct Natural Cushion Cut Diamond: Blue Nile Prices

Natural 2.5ct GIA cushion diamonds represent the point in the market where price escalation becomes exponential. The jump from natural 2ct F-VVS2 Ideal ($13,679) to natural 2.5ct G-VS1 Ideal ($19,375) is not proportional to the 25% weight increase — it reflects the compounding rarity premium above the 2ct weight threshold.

**Natural 2.5ct colour guidance.** At 8.5mm face-up, body colour in a cushion modified brilliant is visible in platinum and white gold settings. F colour is the recommended minimum for white metal at 2.5ct — G colour in white gold can show warmth in the stone's culet and lower facets under certain lighting. In yellow or rose gold, G-H is appropriate: the warm metal reflection normalises the stone's body colour and buying D-F for yellow gold is spending the premium for a colour upgrade the setting nullifies.

**Natural 2.5ct clarity minimum.** VS1 is the reliably safe floor at 2.5ct — all VS1 cushion modified brilliants at 8.5mm are eye-clean without confirmation. VS2 at 2.5ct requires individual HD video verification: inclusions that hide at 7.5mm become visible at 8.5mm depending on type and placement. SI1 is not recommended at 2.5ct without jeweller-confirmed eye-cleanliness from the actual HD video.

